  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "REF Onsite Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities including but not limited to:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Install, repair, and maintain refrigeration systems, including refrigerators, and some others prism products.</li><li>Diagnose and troubleshoot system issues, including mechanical, electrical, and refrigerantrelated problems.</li><li>Repair or replace faulty components, such as compressors, condensers, evaporators, motors, and fans.</li><li>Perform regular preventive maintenance on refrigeration systems to ensure optimal performance and prevent breakdowns.</li><li>Conduct system tests to verify performance, temperature control, and refrigerant levels.</li><li>Calibrate temperature controls,thermostats, and pressure switches as needed.</li><li>Follow safety protocols and guidelines to ensure a safe working environment.</li><li>Adhere to relevant regulations, codes, and industry standards for handling refrigerants and electrical systems.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of repairs, maintenance activities, and parts inventory.</li><li>Provide excellent customer service by addressing client inquiries and resolving issues promptly.</li><li>Stay updated with advancements in refrigeration technology, industry trends, and best practices.</li><li>Collaborate with team members and contractors to complete projects and assignments.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by superior/or managery.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Min O-Level or equivalent.Relevant certifications or vocational training is a plus.</li><li>Min 2 years’ experience as a Refrigeration Technician or similar role.</li><li>Strong knowledge of refrigeration systems and components.</li><li>Familiarity with electrical systems and troubleshooting techniques.</li><li>Ability to read and interpret technical manuals and diagrams.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.</li><li>Detail-oriented with a strong commitment to quality and safety.</li><li>Excellent communication and customer service skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and under pressure.</li><li>Possess Class 3 License would be an added advantage</li></ul>",
